    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - REMOVE - INPUT SHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1301703" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the front bearing cover is still installed, remove the six (6) retaining bolts and cover.
                Remove any remaining gasket material from the case and cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301751">Figure 51</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301751" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301751" filename="../figg13/g1301751.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 51. Input Shaft Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bearing retaining snap ring from the input shaft groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301751">Figure 51</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drive the input shaft toward the case rear as far as possible. Pull the input shaft forward
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301752">Figure 52</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301752" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301752" filename="../figg13/g1301752.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 52. Pull Input Shaft Forward</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use pry bars to complete removal of the bearing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive gear spacer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301753">Figure 53</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301753" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301753" filename="../figg13/g1301753.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 53. Remove Drive Gear Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive gear internal snap ring
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301754">Figure 54</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301754" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301754" filename="../figg13/g1301754.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 54. Internal Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the input shaft forward and out of the drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301755">Figure 55</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301755" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301755" filename="../figg13/g1301755.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 55. Input Shaft Out Of Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive gear from inside the case.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the bushing in the input shaft pocket and replace if necessary.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
